author: Nicole Saavedra
title: Jefferson, Prince Avenue Christian hang on to spots in high school football poll
text:
Jefferson, Prince Avenue Christian hang on to spots in high school football poll Jefferson and Prince Avenue Christian stayed put in the Georgia Sports Writers Association football poll, which was released Tuesday. 
Jefferson (6-0, 2-0 in Region 8-AAA) is ranked third in Class AAA after posting a 27-8 win over Elbert County (5-1, 1-1) Friday. Elbert County was ranked fourth heading into the pivotal region game with Jefferson, and dropped to seventh this week following the loss. Jefferson will host Morgan County at 7:30 p.m. Friday. Oconee County is also receiving votes. 
Prince Avenue (6-0, 4-0 in Region 8-A) is second in Class A following a 35-14 win over Commerce Friday. The Wolverines will host Athens Academy (5-0, 3-0) on Friday.
